# Line Notify — Placeholder

This directory is reserved for the Line Notify provider.

When implementing, follow the Provider Extension Guide in `scripts/notify/README.md`.

## Quick Start

1. Copy this directory structure from `scripts/telegram-notify/`:
   ```
   scripts/line-notify/
     hook.sh
     install.sh
     update.sh
     uninstall.sh
   ```

2. Implement `hook.sh` using the interface defined in `scripts/notify/README.md`.

3. Use config key prefix `LINE_` (e.g., `LINE_ENABLED`, `LINE_NOTIFY_TOKEN`).

4. Deploy hook to `~/.config/ai-notify/hooks/line-notify.sh` from `install.sh`.

## Line Notify API Reference

- Token endpoint: `https://notify-api.line.me/api/notify`
- Auth header: `Authorization: Bearer <LINE_NOTIFY_TOKEN>`
- POST field: `message=<text>`

```bash
curl --silent --max-time 10 \
  -X POST "https://notify-api.line.me/api/notify" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer ${LINE_NOTIFY_TOKEN}" \
  --data-urlencode "message=${MESSAGE}" \
  || true
```
